6 An Act relating to state government; creating the
Statewide Official Compensation Commission; providing
7 for membership of commission; authorizing meetings
based on meetings of the Board on Legislative
8 Compensation; requiring Statewide Official
Compensation Commission to set salaries for certain
9 public officials; prohibiting modification of salary
amounts in contravention of Section 10 of Article
10 XXIII of the Oklahoma Constitution; amending 74 O.S.
2021, Section 250.4, which relates to state officer
11 salaries; providing for operative effect of salary
provisions; providing for effect of action taken by
12 Statewide Official Compensation Commission; repealing
74 O.S. 2021, Section 250.4, which relates to public
13 official compensation; providing for codification;
and providing effective dates.
14
15
16
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
19 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 291.4 of Title 74, unless there
20 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
21 A. There is hereby created the Statewide Official Compensation
22 Commission.
23 B. The Statewide Official Compensation Commission shall consist
24 of the same persons who constitute the Board on Legislative
ENGR. H. B. NO. 2674 Page 1
1 Comp ensation as provided by Section 21 of Article V of the Oklahoma
2 Constitution.
3 C. The Statewide Official Compensation Commission shall be
4 authorized to meet only on the same date as the Board on Legislative
5 Compensation.
6 D. The Statewide Official Compensation Commission shall set the
7 salary for each of the following elected officials:
8 1. The Governor;
9 2. The Lieutenant Governor;
10 3. The Attorney General;
11 4. The State Treasurer;
12 5. The State Auditor and Inspector;
13 6. The Superintendent of Public Instruction;
14 7. The State Insurance Commissioner;
15 8. The Commissioner of Labor; and
16 9. The members of the Oklahoma Corporation Commission.
17 E. The Statewide Official Compensation Commission shall not set
18 the salary for any of the officials identified in subsection D of
19 this section at an amount less than the salary in effect for such
20 officials as of January 1, 2025.
21 F. At its authorized meeting, the Statewide Official
22 Compensation Commission shall set the salary for each of the
23 officials identified in subsection D of this section for any term of
24
ENGR. H. B. NO. 2674 Page 2
1 offi ce for such officials beginning on or after the date as of which
2 the Commission sets the salary amount.
3 G. The Statewide Official Compensation Commission shall not
4 modify a salary amount in violation of the requirements of Section
5 10 of Article XXIII of the Oklahoma Constitution.
6 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 74 O.S. 2021, Section 250.4, is
7 amended to read as follows:
8 Section 250.4. A. Pursuant to provisions of the Constitution
9 of the State of Oklahoma from and after the beginning date of a term
10 of office which commences in, or after, January 2016, and except as
11 otherwise provided by this section, the following officers of the
12 State of Oklahoma shall be annually compensated for their services,
13 payable monthly, as follows:
14 1. The Governor shall receive a salary of One Hundred Forty-
15 seven Thousand Dollars ($147,000.00);
16 2. The Lieutenant Governor shall receive a salary of One
17 Hundred Fourteen Thousand Seven Hundred Thirteen Dollars
18 ($114,713.00);
19 3. The Attorney General shall receive a salary of One Hundred
20 Thirty-two Thousand Eight Hundred Twenty-five Dollars ($132,825.00);
21 4. The State Superintendent of Public Instruction shall receive
22 a salary of One Hundred Twenty-four Thousand Three Hundred Seventy-
23 three Dollars ($124,373.00);
24
ENGR. H. B. NO. 2674 Page 3
1 5. Each member of the Corporation Commission shall receive a
2 salary of One Hundred Fourteen Thousand Seven Hundred Thirteen
3 Dollars ($114,713.00);
4 6. The State Treasurer shall receive a salary of One Hundred
5 Fourteen Thousand Seven Hundred Thirteen Dollars ($114,713.00);
6 7. The State Auditor and Inspector shall receive a salary of
7 One Hundred Fourteen Thousand Seven Hundred Thirteen Dollars
8 ($114,713.00);
9 8. The State Insurance Commissioner shall receive a salary of
10 One Hundred Fourteen Thousand Seven Hundred Thirteen Dollars
11 ($114,713.00); and
12 9. The Commissioner of Labor shall receive a salary of One
13 Hundred Five Thousand Fifty-three Dollars ($105,053.00).
14 B. With respect to any public official whose salary is provided
15 for by this section, the provisions of this section shall be
16 operative until the Statewide Official Compensation Commission
17 modifies the salary amount for such official. If the Statewide
18 Official Compensation Commission modifies the salary amount as
19 otherwise prescribed by this section, the order of the Commission
20 shall supersede the provisions of this section with respect to the
21 appliable statewide elected official.
22 SECTION 3. REPEALER 74 O.S. 2021, Section 250.4, as
23 amended by Section 2 of this act, is hereby repealed.
24
ENGR. H. B. NO. 2674 Page 4
1 SECTION 4. Sections 1 and 2 of this act shall become effective
2 November 1, 2025.
3 SECTION 5. Section 3 of this act shall become effective January
4 31, 2030.
